<subSubSection id="C3156538603EFFC6B8E7D5B3FF190F84" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BB036B3603EFFC6B8E7D5B3FD380C83" blockId="9.[151,1437,223,754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B8E7D5B3FE6F0D8F" bold="true" box="[151,388,223,249]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Material examined.</emphasis>
Wonju-si (
<geoCoordinate id="EE3B5074603EFFC6BA77D58DFD5B0D8A" box="[519,688,225,252]" degrees="37" direction="north" minutes="22" orientation="latitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" precision="1" seconds="34.1" value="37.376137">37°22′ 34.1″N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE3B5074603EFFC6BACFD5B3FC970D8A" box="[703,892,223,252]" degrees="127" direction="east" minutes="51" orientation="longitude" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" precision="1" seconds="15.2" value="127.85422">127° 51′ 15.2″E</geoCoordinate>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3187623603EFFC6BBE4D5B3FBC30D8C" box="[916,1064,223,250]" name="South Korea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">South Korea</collectingCountry>
. Collected by Chi-Woo Lee (
<date id="FFB11073603EFFC6BD0FD5B3FECC0C68" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" value="2015-03-25">25 March 2015</date>
). Three female specimens examined (
<collectionCode id="ED1EAE76603EFFC6BAA9D46FFCD80C6B" box="[729,819,259,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">NNIBR</collectionCode>
90880–90882). By our observation, no morphological differences were found between 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6BA79D44BFCAA0C37" box="[521,833,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BA79D44BFD750C37" box="[521,670,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Eobathynella</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BABCD444FCAA0C37" box="[716,833,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">yeojuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6BB87D444FB670C37" box="[1015,1164,296,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BB87D444FB670C37" box="[1015,1164,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">E. yeojuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, we consider that the studied specimens to correspond to 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BA2DD420FD100C13" box="[605,763,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6BA2DD420FD1D0C13" box="[605,758,332,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">E. yeojuensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, considering that subterranean taxa including the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6B8E7D403FE8B0CFF" authorityName="Noodt" authorityYear="1965" box="[151,352,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Parabathynellidae</taxonomicName>
have many cryptic species that are difficult to distinguish based only on morphological characteristics and have been regarded as short-range endemics because of their small spatial distributions (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B42603EFFC6BCA4D4FFFA7C0CDB" author="Guzik, M. T. &amp; Abrams, K. M. &amp; Cooper, S. J. B. &amp; Humphreys, W. F. &amp; Cho, J. L. &amp; Austin, A. D." box="[1236,1431,403,430]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" pagination="205 - 216" refId="ref5358" refString="Guzik, M. T., Abrams, K. M., Cooper, S. J. B., Humphreys, W. F., Cho, J. L. &amp; Austin, A. D. (2008) Phylogeography of the ancient Parabathynellidae (Crustacea: Bathynellacea) from the Yilgarn region of Western Australia. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 205 - 216. [https: // www. publish. csiro. au / is / IS 07040]" type="journal article" year="2008">
Guzik 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BD50D4F8FABB0CDB" box="[1312,1360,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B42603EFFC6B8E7D4DBFEB50CA7" author="Perina, G. &amp; Camacho, A. I. &amp; Huey, J. &amp; Horwitz, P. &amp; Koenders, A." box="[151,350,439,466]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" pagination="423 - 447" refId="ref6020" refString="Perina, G., Camacho, A. I., Huey, J., Horwitz, P. &amp; Koenders, A. (2018) Understanding subterranean variability: the first genus of Bathynellidae (Bathynellacea, Crustacea) from Western Australia described through a morphological and multigene approach. Invertebrate Systematics, 32, 423 - 447. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 17004" type="journal article" year="2018">
Perina 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B895D4D4FEFE0CA7" box="[229,277,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), we cannot be completely certain that they are the same species until compared to molecular data from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6B8A5D4B0FE820C83" box="[213,361,476,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B8A5D4B0FE820C83" box="[213,361,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">E. yeojuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from the 
<typeStatus id="54B48811603EFFC6BA32D4B0FD990C80" box="[578,626,476,502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB036B3603EFFC6B8B7D493FF190F84" blockId="9.[151,1437,223,754]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B8B7D493FE440F6F" bold="true" box="[199,431,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Molecular analysis.</emphasis>
We sequenced and analyzed DNA extracted from three 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6BC54D76CFB370F6F" authority="Ji &amp; Min, 2022" authorityName="Ji &amp; Min" authorityYear="2022" box="[1060,1244,512,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gwangjuensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BC54D76CFB370F6F" box="[1060,1244,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">E. gwangjuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6BC93D493FAD60F6F" bold="true" box="[1251,1341,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24857DA603EFFC6BC93D493FAD60F6F" box="[1251,1341,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and one 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6B8E7D74FFE240F4B" box="[151,463,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B8E7D74FFEC70F4B" box="[151,300,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Eobathynella</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B92AD748FE240F4B" box="[346,463,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">yeojuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen (
<tableCitation id="C68D0308603EFFC6BA21D74FFD4D0F4B" box="[593,678,547,573]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,512,536]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Data used for molecular analysis. Sequences marked with an asterisk were obtained for the first time in the present study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF70663B6035FFCDB8E7D76CFEC10F4A" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" tableUuid="DF70663B6035FFCDB8E7D76CFEC10F4A">Table 1</tableCitation>
). A total of 1,406 bp for 18S rDNA and 792 bp for CO1 were obtained. The intraspecific genetic distance between the three individuals of the new species ranged from 0.0 to 0.5% for CO1 and were all identical for 18S rDNA sequences. The pairwise genetic distance between the new species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D30603EFFC6B8E7D7E3FE3B0FDF" box="[151,464,655,681]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parabathynellidae" genus="Eobathynella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Bathynellacea" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yeojuensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B8E7D7E3FEC70FDF" box="[151,300,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Eobathynella</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97BEAA1603EFFC6B92BD7FCFE3B0FDF" box="[347,464,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">yeojuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 4% for 18S rDNA and 21.8–22.0% for CO1. We constructed a maximum likelihood tree for selected parabathynellid genera based on 417 bp of CO1 and 952 bp of 18S rRNA gene sequences (
<figureCitation id="13342A36603EFFC6B8D0D7BBFF0F0F84" box="[160,228,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[249,1338,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[249,1339,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. A maximum likelihood analysis on the parabathynellid genera. Numbers on nodes represent bootstrap values from 1,000 replications.Information of the molecular data used for the molecular analysis is provided in Table 1. (A) phylogenetic tree based on mitochondrial 18S rRNA sequences (952 bp); (B) phylogenetic tree based on mitochondrial CO1 sequences (417 bp)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571895/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
